ngo**. Across the curve, Brent time spreads are now largely weaker than they were pre-war.", "time": "07:09", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 73754, "likes": 349, "replies": 13, "retweets": 48, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 40, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067145274305224843", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067145274305224843", "text": "\"... every day WTI is above $70...\"", "time": "07:20", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 106955, "likes": 174, "replies": 33, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 23, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067158019285368906", "url": "https://x.com/CRUDEOIL231/status/2067158019285368906", "text": "Here’s how the leaked barrels are shaping up so far. Stripping out Iran, the flow cleared the market at a clip of around 3mb/d through June.\n\n#oott #iran https://t.co/2ukEIpRngy", "time": "08:10", "author": "CRUDEOIL231", "author_name": "JH", "followers": 59314, "views": 30855, "likes": 270, "replies": 11, "retweets": 46, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 70, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067160464543420806", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067160464543420806", "text": "At current oil prices, if Iran reverts to pre-war exports (that's my assumption), Tehran would make $60-$70 billion a year in crude and other oil liquids revenue.  With the MoU waivers on offer, Iran could be able to repatriate that money. \n\nPallets and pallets of oil money.", "time": "08:20", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 218705, "likes": 782, "replies": 43, "retweets": 134, "quotes": 21, "bookmarks": 67, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2067162216155992552", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067162216155992552", "text": "CHART OF THE DAY: In its first look into 2027, @IEA sees the return of an oil glut. The Paris-based agency warns of higher-than-normal uncertainty about its  supply and demand forecasts, but with expected Hormuz reopening, by this time next year, it sees too much oil — again. https://t.co/aGqqZ7mvot", "time": "08:27", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 61282, "likes": 311, "replies": 32, "retweets": 75, "quotes": 18, "bookmarks": 80, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2067203509376922019", "url": "https://x.com/antonisbabo/status/2067203509376922019", "text": "#oott outfit of the ton ㅋㅋ https://t.co/VFtfvCFJiz", "time": "11:11", "author": "antonisbabo", "author_name": "바보", "followers": 39618, "views": 18247, "likes": 570, "replies": 0, "retweets": 179, "quotes": 15, "bookmarks": 44, "labels": {"relevant": false, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2067234942019633424", "url": "https://x.com/DarioCpx/status/2067234942019633424", "text": "JustDarioDaily - Podcast\n\n⚠️ The Oil Market Is Betting On An Impossible Trump's Miracle 🎙️ \n\n- Trump rush to reopen Hormuz\n- The grim reality traders are ignoring\n\n#OOTT\n\nhttps://t.co/n1SGrk8j7M", "time": "13:16", "author": "DarioCpx", "author_name": "JustDario", "followers": 113106, "views": 131663, "likes": 194, "replies": 17, "retweets": 23, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 36, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Iran", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2067283716947214476", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067283716947214476", "text": "US President Trump says some things aren't mentioned in the MoU but are \"understood\" between the US and Iran.", "time": "16:30", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 29517, "likes": 124, "replies": 24, "retweets": 7, "quotes": 10, "bookmarks": 10, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2067288737604661422", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067288737604661422", "text": "US President Trump: \n\n\"... I want to thank China, President Xi, he stayed neutral, totally neutral, and I appreciated it; and I want to thank Vladimir Putin, he was very neutral. They could have made it much more difficult for us...\"", "time": "16:50", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 95486, "likes": 336, "replies": 34, "retweets": 53, "quotes": 31, "bookmarks": 43, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067289450653131126", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067289450653131126", "text": "US President Trump on the Iranian funds:\n\n\"... We have their money. It's not our money, it's their money. And we froze it. And at a certain point in time,  I guess we are going to have to give it back. If we didn't give it back, nobody would ever invest in the dollar again...\"", "time": "16:53", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 43961, "likes": 388, "replies": 26, "retweets": 52, "quotes": 18, "bookmarks": 34, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2067360859039650011", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067360859039650011", "text": "The key paragraph of the US-Iran MoU about the Strait of Hormuz (as read it to the press by a senior American official): \n\n“5-Upon the signing of this MoU, the Islamic Republic of Iran will make arrangements using its best efforts for the safe passage of commercial vessels with no charge for 60 days", "time": "21:36", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 112970, "likes": 272, "replies": 26, "retweets": 62, "quotes": 21, "bookmarks": 66, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2067366563573879187", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067366563573879187", "text": "BREAKING: The US-Iran MoU was signed digitally by the presidents of both nations tonight, Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman says on state television.\n\nThe previously scheduled signing ceremony in Geneva for Friday won’t go ahead anymore, although the delegations will still meet.", "time": "21:59", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 69743, "likes": 410, "replies": 19, "retweets": 97, "quotes": 13, "bookmarks": 26, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 41, "views": 149346, "likes": 471}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 16, "views": 24893, "likes": 124}, {"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 11, "views": 985494, "likes": 3492}, {"username": "CDCapMan", "name": "CD Capital Management", "followers": 164, "tweets": 4, "views": 1166, "likes": 12}, {"username": "LiveSquawk", "name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 436347, "tweets": 4, "views": 31617, "likes": 46}], "top_authors_by_views": [{"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 11, "views": 985494, "likes": 3492}, {"us